HEADWORD: Lozengy
<hw>Loz"en*gy</hw> <pr>(-⟦ecr⟧n*j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>losang⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Lozenge</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Divided into lozenge-shaped compartments, as the
field or a bearing, by lines drawn in the direction of the bend
sinister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

